title: NASA Probe Reveals Size and Shape of Styx, Pluto's Smallest Moon
text: Earlier this year, on July 14, NASA's New Horizons probe made space exploration history when, after traveling through space for nearly a decade, it at long last reached the edge of our Solar System and flew by Pluto and its accompanying moons.
